Batting fourth, third baseman, Tachibana.

117
00:09:32,060 --> 00:09:35,980
Well, you could also say that 
my best friend has a big heart.

118
00:09:35,980 --> 00:09:37,510
What are you talking about ?

119
00:09:37,510 --> 00:09:40,600
I'm talking about us spending the night together after the concert.

120
00:09:42,000 --> 00:09:42,600
Ball.

121
00:09:43,650 --> 00:09:46,200
Because you told him
 about it, it saved me.

122
00:09:47,400 --> 00:09:51,650
I thought about telling him. 
He called me after I came home.

123
00:09:51,650 --> 00:09:55,500
But it was from camp, and
 his seniors were teasing him.

124
00:09:55,500 --> 00:09:57,420
So he hung up right away.

125
00:10:16,700 --> 00:10:19,000
He really is a big-shot.

126
00:10:20,380 --> 00:10:23,700
If I were him, I wouldn't 
be feeling at peace.

127
00:10:34,100 --> 00:10:35,150
Out.

128
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,220
What happened ?

129
00:10:40,220 --> 00:10:41,650
Well...

130
00:10:41,650 --> 00:10:44,170
...it looks like he forgot
 to step on home plate.

131
00:10:47,790 --> 00:10:49,910
Even then, he went 3 for 4.

132
00:10:49,910 --> 00:10:53,170
If he had that homerun,
it would have been for the cycle.

133
00:10:53,990 --> 00:10:54,350
Ugh !

134
00:11:25,290 --> 00:11:25,800
EYECATCH

135
00:11:32,750 --> 00:11:35,470
He attacked me first.

136
00:11:35,470 --> 00:11:41,010
I don't know who's at fault here, but it's clear who's stronger.

137
00:11:46,250 --> 00:11:48,590
Picking on the weak isn't cool.

138
00:11:50,180 --> 00:11:53,600
When I fight, I fight to the end.

139
00:11:55,150 --> 00:11:58,800
Or are you going
 to pick up this fight ?

140
00:11:58,800 --> 00:12:03,450
You'd better refrain.
It's clear who's stronger.

141
00:12:03,670 --> 00:12:04,060
...?

142
00:12:07,290 --> 00:12:08,800
Baseball club ?

143
00:12:08,800 --> 00:12:10,400
Just established.

144
00:12:11,110 --> 00:12:14,440
Are you sure that baseball club 
guys can afford to get into a fight ?

145
00:12:14,440 --> 00:12:16,650
Whether it's a baseball club or the tea ceremony club...

146
00:12:16,650 --> 00:12:19,910
...there's no club where its members are allowed to get into a fight.

147
00:12:19,910 --> 00:12:24,000
I have this habit where I do practice
 swings without checking my surroundings.

148
00:12:27,300 --> 00:12:30,380
No matter how hard
 you try, it'll be all in vain.

149
00:12:30,380 --> 00:12:34,800
As long as Tachibana Hideo is around, you can never go to the Koushien.

150
00:12:34,800 --> 00:12:40,050
Hard work is never wasted,
even if it doesn't lead to the Koushien.

151
00:12:46,700 --> 00:12:50,400
I don't know what he was like as a child, but I wouldn't want to hang out with him.

152
00:13:01,400 --> 00:13:03,000
Aim for the Koushien ! 
Tachibana Hideo

153
00:13:01,600 --> 00:13:02,600
0:04:02.00 0:04:03.00  

154
00:13:11,000 --> 00:13:11,800
Hide-chan.

155
00:13:15,590 --> 00:13:16,950
He's not here.

156
00:13:17,220 --> 00:13:17,720
...?

157
00:13:50,930 --> 00:13:52,680
Do you want a piece of apple ?

158
00:13:54,540 --> 00:13:56,700
I don't want a piece of apple.

159
00:13:57,240 --> 00:13:57,970
Oh, I see.

160
00:13:59,020 --> 00:14:00,340
Who are you ?

161
00:14:01,370 --> 00:14:06,150
Sagawa Shuuji.
 I'm Hide-chan's childhood friend.

162
00:14:06,150 --> 00:14:10,750
We used to be good friends.
 We always did things together.

163
00:14:10,750 --> 00:14:14,700
What was mine was Hide-chan's. What was Hide-chan's was mine.

164
00:14:15,450 --> 00:14:18,810
If you come any closer,
 I'm going to shout.

165
00:14:18,810 --> 00:14:20,970
You shouldn't do that.

166
00:14:20,970 --> 00:14:25,030
It'll be dangerous if I get startled and my hand slips as I peel the apple.

167
00:14:33,640 --> 00:14:34,600
Oh, a cockroach.

168
00:14:35,450 --> 00:14:37,600
That's such an overused tactic.

169
00:14:37,600 --> 00:14:38,200
It's flying.

170
00:14:39,080 --> 00:14:40,220
Stop that already...

171
00:14:49,050 --> 00:14:49,880
Shit !

172
00:14:51,640 --> 00:14:53,330
Hey ! Open up !

173
00:14:55,590 --> 00:14:56,900
What's the ruckus ?

174
00:14:56,900 --> 00:14:58,650
You're being a nuisance to the neighbors.

175
00:15:00,760 --> 00:15:02,400
Hey.

176
00:15:03,480 --> 00:15:04,550
Hi, Hiro.

177
00:15:04,550 --> 00:15:06,240
Do you want an apple ?

178
00:15:07,550 --> 00:15:09,200
You little...! It's mine !

179
00:15:12,130 --> 00:15:13,400
Sorry about that.

180
00:15:13,400 --> 00:15:16,600
I have this habit where I do practice 
swings without checking my surroundings.

181
00:15:17,460 --> 00:15:18,480
Here.

182
00:15:23,180 --> 00:15:25,930
If you have a message
 for Hideo, I'll take it.

183
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:37,320
Tell him to work hard and become more famous.

184
00:15:37,320 --> 00:15:42,660
Tachibana Hideo is
 the pride of us brothers.

185
00:15:48,660 --> 00:15:49,400
Brothers ?

186
00:16:51,530 --> 00:16:53,450
Oh, welcome home, Hide-chan.

187
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:54,980
What are you doing ?

188
00:16:54,980 --> 00:16:57,500
Can't you tell ?
 We're comparing heights.

189
00:16:58,430 --> 00:17:01,200
I'm just trying to figure out how much taller I'm going to get.

190
00:17:01,200 --> 00:17:02,500
Do it in your room.

191
00:17:06,830 --> 00:17:09,300
Here. It's something your 
childhood friend left behind.

192
00:17:10,500 --> 00:17:12,780
He was here ?

193
00:17:12,780 --> 00:17:16,700
He seems like a tough fighter, but he seems to dislike cockroaches.

194
00:17:17,790 --> 00:17:20,040
He was already in the room. I was taken by surprise.

195
00:17:21,100 --> 00:17:24,050
I almost shouted.

196
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:27,010
I was surprised, too, to see him for the first time in a long while.



197
00:17:35,730 --> 00:17:37,210
Okay, let's pull ourselves together.

198
00:17:37,210 --> 00:17:38,120
Let's go !

199
00:17:38,120 --> 00:17:39,360
One more !

200
00:17:52,290 --> 00:17:54,950
He's working overtime today, too.

201
00:18:15,490 --> 00:18:16,200
Hikari !

202
00:18:16,200 --> 00:18:17,000
Hey !

203
00:18:17,000 --> 00:18:18,660
Hikari, let's walk home together.

204
00:18:18,660 --> 00:18:19,270
Yeah.

205
00:18:20,600 --> 00:18:20,810


206
